main event: An unidentified object that emitted a dull, greyish-colored light was observed flying over Kelly Air Force Base, Texas.
interesting points: The object was oval-shaped and appeared to be approximately one-third the size of a full moon.
The object emitted a dull reddish glow and was estimated to be at an altitude of 10,000 to 15,000 feet and a distance of approximately 5 miles.
The object moved at an estimated speed of 300 to 400 mph and was visible for approximately one minute.
No physical evidence of a crash or landing was observed, and the object left no visible trail or exhaust vapor.
The object was observed by several airmen from the 75th AD Wing at Kelly Air Force Base.
sighted object: an oval-shaped object emitting a dull, greyish-colored light
